text: Katie Carter-Gutierrez (born October 10, 1985) is an American volleyball player and coach. She played at the 2011–12 CEV Women's Challenge Cup, winning a silver medal, and 2018 CEV Volleyball Challenge Cup. She grew up in Steamboat Springs, Colorado. She played for University of California, Los Angeles's women's volleyball team. She played for Criollas de Caguas, Club Voleibol Aguere, Volero Zurich, Agel Prostejov, Dicle Üniversitesi Spor Kulübü, Polluelas de Aibonito, and VBN Nantes. == References == == Other websites == * Katie Carter - United States Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players Category:American volleyball coaches Category:Sportspeople from Colorado
